THERE were mixed emotions in Mogale City yesterday when a new mayor was announced. Residents of the municipality in Gauteng were shocked to hear last week that DA mayor Lynn Pannall had resigned for medical reasons. Yesterday the councillor committee gathered to elect a new mayor. The council sitting was tense as councillors chose between the DA&rsquo;s Michael Holenstein and the ANC&rsquo;s Naga Lipudi. The committee was made up of representatives from the ANC, DA, EFF and IFP. It was announced yesterday afternoon that Holenstein had been elected the new mayor.Mogale City spokesman Nkosana Zau told Daily Sun: &ldquo;The mayor will have to overcome a housing backlog and high unemployment, especially among the youth.&rdquo;